vectorData.altText: 5. Presume this is the fourth thoracic vertebra. Which rib articulates at A?
That's right!  Ribs are enumerated by the vertebra below.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Pick up two thoracic vertebrae and articulate them with each other.  
Now articulate the rib you’ve been studying with the vertebrae in your hand.
Notice that the crest on the head of the rib articulates with the site where the intervertebral disc would be located.
The tubercular facet of the rib articulates with the costal facet of the transverse process of the numerically corresponding vertebra;
i.e. the tubercular facet of the sixth rib articulates with the costal facet on the transverse process of the sixth rib.
